value.value: A heart disease and a myopathy that is characterized by deterioration of the function of the heart muscle.

An epilepsy syndrome that is a group of clinical entities showing a cluster of electro-clinical characteristics, classified according to age at onset, cognitive and developmental antecedents and consequences, motor and sensory examinations, EEG features, provoking or triggering factors, and patterns of seizure occurrence with respect to sleep.
An electroclinical syndrome with onset in the neonatal period less than 44 weeks of gestational age.
An electroclinical syndrome with onset in infancy occurring between birth and one year of age.
An electroclinical syndrome with onset in childhood between one and 12 years of age.
An electroclinical syndrome with onset in adolescence and adulthood.

label.value: variable age at onset electroclinical syndrome

value.value: An electroclinial syndrome that is characterized by development of seizures later in life with a variable age of onset and duration.
A childhood electroclinical syndrome characterized by the occurrence of typical absence seizures starting between the age of four and ten years.
A neonatal period electroclinical syndrome that is characterized by tonic spasms and partial seizures.

An amino acid metabolic disorder that is classified by inadequate levels of the enzyme 3-methylcrotonyl-CoA carboxylase that helps break down proteins containing the amino acid leucine. This disease has_symptom muscular hypotonia (weak muscle tone), has_symptom muscular atrophy, has_symptom feeding difficulties, has_symptom recurrent episodes of vomiting and diarrhea, and has_symptom lethargy.
An iron metabolism disease that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the ceruloplasmin gene characterized by progressive neurodegeneration of the retina and basal ganglia and diabetes mellitus.
An amino acid metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the GATM gene resulting in deficiency of arginine:glycine amidinotransferase which then limits creatine synthesis.
A cytochrome-c oxidase deficiency disease characterized by myotonia, abnormalities of the heart and kidneys, and lactic acidosis.

label.value: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblC

value.value: A methylmalonic acidemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency in synthesis of both AdoCbl and MeCbl (cblC) and is characterized by decreased levels of the coenzymes adenosylcobalamin (AdoCbl) and methylcobalamin (MeCbl), which results in decreased activity of the respective enzymes methylmalonyl-CoA mutase.

label.value: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblD

value.value: A methylmalonic aciduria that is characterized by combined homocystinuria and methylmalonic aciduria and deficiency of MCM and MS activities.

label.value: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblF

value.value: A methylmalonic acidemia that is characterized by the accumulation of cobalamin in lysosomes which is then unable to synthesize the cofactors adenosylcobalamin (AdoCbl) and methylcobalamin (MeCbl) and that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the LMBRD1 gene on chromosome 6q13.
An inherited metabolic disorder resulting from a deficiency in vitamin or vitamin cofactor transport or metabolism.

A vitamin metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in mutations in the folate receptor 1 (FOLR1) gene coding for folate receptor alpha (FRalpha), is located_in the brain and is characterized by progressive movement disturbance, psychomotor decline, and epilepsy.
An amino acid metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in deficiency of ornithine translocase resulting in the accumulation of ammonia in the blood.
An amino acid metabolic disorder that has_material_basis_in defects in the biosynthesis of the amino acid L-serine.
A serine deficiency that has_material_basis_in deficiency of phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase which results in a disruption of L-serine biosynthesis.
A serine deficiency that has_material_basis_in deficiency of phosphoserine aminotransferase and is characterized by low concentartions of serine and flycine in plasma and cerebrospinal fluid.
A serine deficiency that has_material_basis_in deficiency of phosphoserine phosphatase impeding the synthesis of L-serine.

A tyrosinemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency of hepatic tyrosine aminotransferase located_in the liver and is characterized by keratitis, painful palmoplantar hyperkeratosis, mental retardation, and elevated serum tyrosine levels.

A tyrosinemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency of the enzyme fumarylacetoacetate hydrolase resulting in an increase in fumarylacetoacetate which inhibits previous steps in tyrosine degradation leading to an accumulation of tyrosine in the body.
A tyrosinemia that has_material_basis_in deficiency of 4-hydroxyphenylpyruvate dioxygenase disrupting the break down of tyrosine.
A carbohydrate metabolism disorder that is characterized by abnormal accumulation or depletion of liver glycogen.
A lipid storage disease that is characterized by accumulation of triglycerides in the cytoplasm of leukocytes, muscle, liver, fibroblasts, and other tissues.
A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by a deficiency of CoQ10 resulting from reduced biosynthesis.
A vitamin metabolic disorder that results from low blood levels of vitamin B12.

label.value: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblE

value.value: A methylmalonic acidemia that is characterized by megaloblastic anemia, lethargy, failure to thrive, developmental delay, intellectual deficit and seizures, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the MTRR gene on chromosome 5p15 that causes inborn error of vitamin B12 metabolism.

label.value: methylmalonic aciduria and homocystinuria type cblG

value.value: A methylmalonic acidemia that is characterized by megaloblastic anemia, lethargy, failure to thrive, developmental delay, intellectual deficit and seizures, has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the MTR gene on chromosome 1q43 that causes an inborn error of vitamin B12 metabolism.
A vitamin B12 deficiency that is characterized by megaloblastic anemia due to the absence of gastric intrinsic factor which results in abnormal vitamin B12 absorption.
A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in mutations in genes on the X chromosome.
An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by the presence of one disease-associated mutation of a gene which is sufficient to cause the disease.
An autosomal genetic disease that is characterized by the presence of two mutated copies of the gene, both of which must be present in order for the disease or trait to develop.
A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in mutations on the Y chromosome.
A monogenic disease that has_material_basis_in a mutation in a single gene on one of the non-sex chromosomes.
A syndrome that is characterized by hypotonia, congenital fiber type disproportion and dysharmonic skeletal maturation.

A substance dependence that is characterized by tolerance, withdrawal symptoms, increasing use, persistent desire to decrease consumption, time spent obtaining or recovering from alcohol caused by a physical and psychological dependence on alcohol.
A substance dependence that is characterized by a physical dependence on nicotine.
A T-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that has_material_basis_in mature T lymphocytes and natural killer cells.
A non-Hodgkin lymphoma involving aberrant T-cells.
A large B-cell lymphoma that is consisting of medium-sized to large B cells with a diffuse growth pattern.
A B-cell lymphocytic neoplasm due to CD5 positive antigen-naive pregerminal center B-cell within the mantle zone that surrounds normal germinal center follicles.
A B-cell lymphoma arising from the marginal zone of lymphoid tissues that is characterized by the presence of small to medium sized atypical lymphocytes.
A mature T-cell and NK-cell lymphoma includes a group of T-cell lymphomas that develop away from the thymus.
A marginal zone B-cell lymphocyte located_in the spleen comprised of B-cells in place of white pulp.
A T-cell acute lymphocytic leukemia that exhibits an unexplained, chronic (greater than 6 months) elevation in large granular lymphocytes (LGLs) in the peripheral blood.
An amyotrophic lateral sclerosis that has_material_basis_in mutation in the VAPB gene on chromosome 20.
